OL,6,FCaitlen had pre-eclampsia which
OL,7,Fdeveloped into HELLP syndrome, a
OL,8,Fsevere pregnancy complication whereby
OL,9,Fthe placenta attacks the rest of the
OL,10,Fbody, and which can only be treated by
OL,11,Fdelivering the baby as soon as
OL,12,Fpossible.
OL,14,FCaitlen said: "There was about a two
OL,15,Fhour gap between (being told) 'if we
OL,16,Fdon't get baby out now, you're both
OL,17,Fgoing to die.'"
OL,19,FBecause of her condition, she had to
OL,20,Fbe put under general anaesthetic to be
OL,21,Fgiven a C-section.
